 at the hands of corrupt officials. These texts offer compelling witness to the challenges of a community’s need to honor memory and experience. They provide evidence towards the formation and sustenance of Christian identity in the midst of Persian society and culture. Above all, each draws upon scriptural and monastic traditions to weave distinctive portraits of notable literary quality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChristian martyrszIranvSources. 0aChristian saintszIranvSources. 0aMartyrologiesxHistory and criticism. 0aPersecutionzIranvSources. 0aSassanidsxHistoryvSources. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / History.2bisacsh1 aet al., , eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2023 Part 2z978311117804208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertGorgias Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102412740uhttps://doi.org/10.31826/978146324562740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781463245627423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781463245627/original  a978-3-11-102412-7  Gorgias Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-117804-2  DG Plus PP Package 2023 Part 2b2023  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles